                <h3>
                    Map My Brain is a simple website that hosts live brain data from an arduino powered EEG headset.
                    The website is currently a proof of concept, using physically connected hardware to update a
                    mySQL database in real time. </h3>
                <h4>
                    <br><br>
                    To log your own brain data, you'll need the following:<br>
                    1.) <a href="http://store.neurosky.com/products/mindflex">A Neurosky brand EEG headset.</a><br>
                    2.) An Arduino that features at least one hardware serial port.<br>
                    3.) The Arduino IDE brain library, available at:
                    <a href="https://github.com/kitschpatrol/Brain">https://github.com/kitschpatrol/Brain.</a><br>
                    4.) A serial port terminal application - I recommend
                    <a href="http://freeware.the-meiers.org/">CoolTerm</a><br><br>

                    If you'd like to give the project a shot,
                    Frontier Nerds, an IT DIY blogger, has a perfect description of how to dismantle the headset and set up
                    the Arduino brain library sketch.
                    <a href="http://www.frontiernerds.com/brain-hack">http://www.frontiernerds.com/brain-hack</a>


